%N A002472 Number of pairs x,y such that y-x=2, (x,n)=1, (y,n)=1 and 1 <= x <= n.
%C A002472 This is the function phi(n, 2) defined in Alder. - _Michel Marcus_, Nov 14 2017
%C A002472 Number of positive z <= n such that z^2 - 4^j is relatively prime to n (for any particular nonnegative integer j). - _Juri-Stepan Gerasimov_, Oct 14 2025, Nov 02 2025
